text: My morning started with an auntie cutting queue.  The lady in Yu Yi Coffee noticed and quickly brightened my the day by executing my order immediately and even brought the bread to the table. Yu Yi Coffee &Tea Hut has nice owners.  Ordered tea set. Bread is nice, crispy and not too dry. The tea is ok too, not too sweet (healthier version). Reasonably priced.
Must try their butter toast bread! Crispy and close to perfection.
Paid $1.10 for a cup of teh c. Taste a bit diluted but still ok. Service was fast.

Diluted coffee and tea. But $1. ðŸ¤£ Next time will order gao.
But boss and lady boss very friendly.
